ser-settings.md)|  \n|Determine the values of user settings|[How to: Read Application Settings in Visual Basic](../../../../visual-basic/developing-apps/programming/app-settings/how-to-read-application-settings.md)|  \n  \n## See also  \n [Managing Application Settings (.NET)](https://docs.microsoft.com/visualstudio/ide/managing-application-settings-dotnet)   \n [My.Settings Object](../../../../visual-basic/language-reference/objects/my-settings-object.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,74],"content":"Accessing application settings (Visual Basic) | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Accessing application settings (Visual Basic) | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,62]}]},{"pos":[668,713],"content":"Accessing application settings (Visual Basic)","linkify":"Accessing application settings (Visual Basic)","nodes":[{"content":"Accessing application settings (Visual Basic)","pos":[0,45]}]},{"pos":[714,822],"content":"This section contains topics describing the <ph id=\"ph1\">`My.Settings`</ph> object and the tasks it enables you to accomplish.","source":"This section contains topics describing the `My.Settings` object and the tasks it enables you to accomplish."},{"pos":[831,842],"content":"My.Settings","linkify":"My.Settings","nodes":[{"content":"My.Settings","pos":[0,11]}]},{"content":"The properties of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`My.Settings`</ph> object provide access to your application's settings.","pos":[846,935],"source":"The properties of the `My.Settings` object provide access to your application's settings."},{"content":"To add or remove settings, use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> pane of the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Project Designer<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[936,1017],"source":" To add or remove settings, use the **Settings** pane of the **Project Designer**."},{"pos":[1024,1161],"content":"The methods of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`My.Settings`</ph> object allow you to save the current user settings or revert the user settin